SIMPLE: macule
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Macule
<hw>Mac"ule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>macule</ets>.
See <er>Macula</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A spot.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>A blur, or an appearance of a
double impression, as when the paper slips a little; a mackle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Macule</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Macule
<hw>Mac"ule</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>maculer</ets>. See
<er>Maculate</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>To blur; especially
<fld>(Print.)</fld>, to blur or double an impression from type. See
<er>Mackle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maculose</ent>⟦br⟧
